To see why “t4 t5 t4” is not in L(G), note that the start rule is

  S → NT44 NT7

so any three‐terminal yield must split as either

 (1) NT44 ⇒ 1 terminal and NT7 ⇒ 2 terminals,  
 (2) NT44 ⇒ 2 terminals and NT7 ⇒ 1 terminal.

Case (1): NT44 has exactly one terminal rule NT44→'t5', so it cannot yield 't4'.  
Case (2): NT7’s only way to yield a single terminal is via one of its terminal rules NT7→'t1','t2','t5' – never 't4'.  

There is no other way to split three terminals from two children, so “t4 t5 t4” cannot be derived.
